# Command gitsign

## What does this command do:

Keyless Git signing using Sigstore

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: `curl -sSfL https://github.com/sigstore/gitsign/releases/latest/download/gitsign_0.14.0_linux_amd64  -o ~/.local/bin/gitsign && chmod +x ~/.local/bin/gitsign`
For Raspberry Pi install using:
```
# Check current version first:
gh api repos/sigstore/gitsign/releases/latest --jq '.tag_name'
# Download binary directly to ~/.local/bin (replace 0.14.0 with current version if newer):
curl -sSfL https://github.com/sigstore/gitsign/releases/latest/download/gitsign_0.14.0_linux_arm64 -o ~/.local/bin/gitsign && chmod +x ~/.local/bin/gitsign
```
For Mac install using: `brew install sigstore/tap/gitsign`

## Command path

For Fedora run: `~/.local/bin/gitsign`
For Raspberry Pi run: `~/.local/bin/gitsign`
For Mac run: `~/.local/bin/gitsign`

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/sigstore/gitsign

## Command options

# Configure git to use gitsign for commit signing
git config --global commit.gpgsign true
git config --global gpg.x509.program gitsign
git config --global gpg.format x509

# Sign a commit manually (auto-signs when commit.gpgsign=true)
git commit -S -m "signed commit"

# Verify a commit's gitsign signature
gitsign verify \
  --certificate-identity=<your-email@example.com> \
  --certificate-oidc-issuer=https://accounts.google.com \
  HEAD

# Verify using GitHub Actions OIDC issuer
gitsign verify \
  --certificate-identity=https://github.com/<org>/<repo>/.github/workflows/<workflow>.yml@refs/heads/main \
  --certificate-oidc-issuer=https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com \
  HEAD

# Show git log with signature details
git log --show-signature

# Check gitsign version
gitsign version

# Show help
gitsign --help
